column1: 1950's Rock 'N' Roll Knowledge Cards Deck
column8: Find out what you know with this entertaining, casually well-written Q&A deck. Each of its 48 cards has a question (true/false, multiple choice, or interrogatory) on the front; the concise answer appears on the back. Some are relatively easy, with the answer more likely to be hesitating at the tip of your tongue than actually unknown. Others will challenge those who are minimally attuned to the decade's music and its milieu. This deck can lead to raucous multiplayer fun, but it's also a satisfying, meticulously researched read that will send a lot of great music drifting through the reader's head.

column1: A Great and Mighty Wonder SATB Edition
column8: A Great and Mighty Wonder - Perf CD/SATB Score Combination composed by Thomas Fettke. Cantatas. Christmas, Sacred. CD kit. Published by Exaltation Publications (LO.65-1972L). The Christmas story prompts us to a profound sense of awe and wonder. It is a love story conceived in the heart of a great and mighty God before the creation of time. The gospel of Luke records that after the shepherds had seen the newborn Messiah, they spread the word about what they had experienced. All who heard it were amazed! Even first-century witnesses stood in awe of this wondrous event . . . and the story continues to stir the hearts and minds of people who hear it afresh each year. Veteran composer/arranger, Tom Fettke, takes us again to Bethlehem to experience the fulfillment of God&apos;s plan in a humble manger. Beloved and familiar carols along with new texts and melodies are masterfully blended to create a Christmas worship experience as again we are invited to celebrate the great and mighty wonder of God&apos;s love! (Although conceived without a spoken narrative, one is provided as a performance option. ) (Limit one per church).

Kjos Piano Library - Fundamentals of Piano Theory - Three Book Set - Includes..
column8: Fundamentals of Piano Theory is a graded piano theory series that goes far beyond traditional method book materials. column8: All for strings is a comprehensive three-volume method surrounded by a wealth of supplementary materials for teaching and performance.This complete curriculum covers virtually every aspect of beginning through intermediate string study, emphasizing technical skills, rhythmic understanding, and quality musical experiences. Includes Book 2 for Cello (79CO) and Theory Workbook 2 for Cello (85CO). Book 2 devotes many exercises and musical selections to the development of major and minor left hand finger patterns for all string players, as well as shifting for cellists and bassists. New bowing styles are introduced, and more advanced rhythm patterns are incorporated. As in Book 1, a great variety of solos, duets, trios. and ensembles are included - perfect for performance! The Theory Workbook is correlated with the All for Strings method books and is suitable for classroom or individual use. Each page features exercises and games which encompass music fundamentals introduced in the method books. Students start by learning the piano keyboard to increase their understanding of the intervals. They also work with fingering chart exercises so that basic theory can be immediately applied to their instrument. In addition to drawing clefs, notes, key and time signatures, students learn about musical phrases and begin composing. Puzzles and musical math games are also included.

column1: 1960's Rock 'N' Roll Knowledge Cards Deck
column8: Music is a key to memory, and with this entertaining Q&A deck you can exercise your memory and revisit the music that defined the 1960s. Each of its 48 cards has a question on the front; the concise answer is on the back. Some are relatively easy, with the answer more likely to be hesitating at the tip of your tongue than actually unknown. Others will challenge people who are minimally attuned to sixties music and its milieu. This deck can lead to raucous multiplayer fun, but it's also a satisfying read that will send a lot of great music drifting through the reader's head.

column8: Similar in concept to its predecessor, "The Living Last Supper" (55/1110L), this unique presentation of the Christmas story is seen through the eyes of those who witnessed the first Christmas in Bethlehem many years ago. There are brief monologues for ten characters--ranging from Mary and Joseph to members of the Innkeeper's family--interspersed among the seven songs. (Also included are character descriptions, set and staging suggestions, and hints for wardrobe and props). The music is Ruth Elaine Schram at her best: beautiful melodies, thoughtful texts, well-crafted part writing-and includes familiar carols with possible congregational participation. The optional orchestration demands are modest, making it possible for the use of live instruments even on a limited budget. An Accompaniment CD is also available, if desired. column8: The TBX150R Tone Blaster Xtreme Guitar Combo Amp rocks as hard as an Ibanez guitar. 150W pumping into 2 - 12" speakers means you're covered for most venues. 2 discreet channels, each with their own 3-band active EQ and a parametric midrange in second channel gives you tons of tone flexibility. LED indicators for Channel, Reverb, Overdrive and Boost take away any guesswork about how you're set up.

column1: Play Ukulele Fast Pack - Three Book Set - Includes Ukulele Chord Finder, Hal ..
column8: The Hal Leonard Ukulele Method with CD (HL.00695832) is designed for anyone just learning to play ukulele. This comprehensive and easy-to-use beginner's guide by acclaimed performer and uke master Lil' Rev includes many fun songs of different styles to learn and play. The accompanying CD contains 46 tracks of songs for demonstration and play along. Includes: types of ukuleles, tuning, music reading, melody playing, chords, strumming, scales, tremolo, music notation and tablature, a variety of music styles, ukulele history and much more. Easy Songs for Ukulele. (Play the Melodies of 20 Pop, Folk, Country, and Blues Songs) (HL.695904). Play along with your favorite tunes from the Beatles, Elvis, Johnny Cash, Woody Guthrie, Simon & Garfunkel, and more! The songs are presented in the order of difficulty, beginning with simple rhythms and melodies and ending with chords and notes up the neck. You can also strum and sing along using the provided lyrics and ukulele chord diagrams. The audio CD features every song played with guitar accompaniment, so you can hear how each song sounds and then play along when you're ready. Songs include: Tom Dooley, We Shall Overcome, All My Loving, Heart And Soul, The House Of The Rising Sun, Blue Eyes Crying In The Rain, Blue Skies, Eight Days A Week, Goodnight, Irene, Last Night I Had The Strangest Dream, Love Me Tender, Nowhere Man, Ob-la-di, Ob-la-da, This Land Is Your Land, Yesterday, Pastures Of Plenty, Blues Stay Away From Me, I Walk The Line, I'm So Lonesome I Could Cry and Your Cheatin' Heart. Hal Leonard Ukulele Chord Finder. (Easy-to-Use Guide to Over 1,000 Ukulele Chords) (HL.695902). Learn to play chords on the ukulele with this comprehensive yet easy-to-use book. The Ukulele Chord Finder contains over 1,000 chord diagrams for the most important 28 chord types, including three voicings for each chord. Also includes a lesson on chord construction and a fingerboard chart of the ukulele neck!

column1: Suzuki Violin School, Violin Part, With Piano Accompaniment CD - 3 Books with..
column8: The Suzuki Method is based on the principle that all children possess ability and that this ability can be developed and enhanced through a nurturing environment. The important elements of the Suzuki approach to instrumental teaching include the following:an early start (aged 3-4 is normal in most countries); the importance of listening to music; learning to play before learning to read; -the involvement of the parent; a nurturing and positive learning environment; a high standard of teaching by trained teachers; the importance of producing a good sound in a balanced and natural way; core repertoire, used by Suzuki students across the world; social interaction with other children. Suzuki students from all over the world can communicate through the language of music. Volume 4 (AP.30725) includes Lullaby (Tonalization) (F. Schubert); Lullaby (Tonalization) (J. Brahms); Concerto No. 2 in G Major, Op. 13, 3rd Movement (F. Seitz); Concerto No. 5 in D Major, Op. 22, 1st Movement (F.Seitz); Concerto No. 5 in D Major, Op. 22, 3rd Movement (F. Seitz); Concerto in A Minor, 1st Movement, Op. 3, No. 6 (A. Vivaldi/T. Nachez); Concerto in A Minor, 3rd Movement, Op. 3, No. 6 (A. Vivaldi/T. Nachez); Perpetual Motion, "Little Suite No. 6" (K. Bohm); Concerto for Two Violins in D Minor, BWV 1043, 1st Movement, Violin II (J. S. Bach). The revised edition for Suzuki Violin School, Volume 5 (AP.32743) is now available. Like the other revised violin books, the music has been edited by the International Violin Committee. Other features include new engravings in a more easily readable 9 x 12 format and new editing of pieces, including bowings and fingerings. Volume 6 (AP.39270) includes La Folia (A. Corelli/S. Suzuki) * Sonata No. 3 in F Major, HWV 370 (G. F. Handel) * Allegro (J.-H. Fiocco) * Gavotte (J. Ph. Rameau) * Sonata No. 4 in D Major, HWV 371 (G. F. Handel).

column1: Piano Theory and Exercise Pack - Compatible with all Methods - 2 Book Set - I..
column8: John Brimhall's Complete Theory Notebook (M465) is a complete, comprehensive book that covers every aspect of music theory: staves, clefs, note symbols, rests, time signatures, scales, chords, and sharps/flats/accidentals. Used by teachers everywhere for all ages. 28 lessons in all. Also includes quizzes. The most widely used piano technique book ever written, The Virtuoso Pianist (AP.616C) was designed to develop agility and strength in all the fingers as well as flexibility of the wrists. Exercises are sequenced so that in each successive exercise, the fingers are rested from the fatigue caused by the previous one. Translated from the original French, this Masterwork edition includes the complete Exercises 1-60 and is clearly engraved for easy reading. Hanon's original introduction is included. He recommends that a student have at least one year of experience before starting this book.

The very sound and look of this fine Gretsch creation will make you want to free yourself of the damning confines of your office, your cubicle or whatever it is that enslaves you and hop the next train to anywhere with a smile on your face as big as the sky and a song in your heart.

Jackson JS23 Dinky Limited Edition Electric Guitar - Satin Gra
column8: The Jackson JS23 Dinky solidbody electric guitar is built to rock. The JS23 Dinky encapsulates rock 'n' roll attitude with its shark fin inlays and dynamic pickup setup. The arch top basswood body and rosewood fretboard deliver an elegant tone that you'll love feeding through your amp. With a synchronized tremolo and tuning locks to ensure that you never lose your pitch, this electric guitar is a versatile rock machine. So if you need a guitar that is ready to rock with the best of them, the Jackson JS23 Dinky is for you.  Compound-radius fingerboard gives you the best of both worlds The Jackson JS23 Dinky solidbody electric guitar features a rosewood compound radius fingerboard for smooth, fast playing. Down low, your fretting hand will appreciate the 12" radius that keeps things nice and confortable for natural, relaxed chord work. Up top, a 16" radius lays it all out flat for effortless, low-action high-speed runs and monumental string bends without fretting out. You get the best of both worlds with the JS Series JS23 Dinky.  Premium components and construction What makes Jackson the solidbody electric guitar of choice for so many players? Start with the neck: solid maple with a comfortable, fast carve - it's joined to a compound radius fingerboard and optimized for blazing leads and massive chords alike. Jackson guitar bodies are designed with killer tone and eye-catching looks in mind, providing distinctive body shapes while staying lightweight enough to play all night. Wanna talk tone? This Jackson JS23 Dinky is fitted with a Jackson high-output humbucker and two low-noise single-coils that deliver a huge sonic palette - from bell-like chime to fat 'n' snarling.

column1: pBone PBONE1BLK Jiggs Plastic Trombone, Black
column8: The Jiggs Whigham pBone brings a fun and intriguing twist to the traditional trombone. With its plastic construction, this lightweight instrument sounds remarkably like typical brass trombones. The pBone features a .500-inch bore design with an ergonomic grip for comfort and an overall weight of only 1.8 pounds. The pBone features a fiberglass slide with brass slide stockings on the inner handslide to keep the slide moving freely. The handslide with feel smoother the more you play the instrument, and you can even play the instrument without the need for slide lubrication. The Jiggs pBone includes a plastic mouthpiece and carrying bag and is available in various colors.
